		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Add a negative chroma signal, delayed by 90 degrees, to the composite signal.<br /></div>Wut?<br /><br />Composite = Luma + Chroma<br />Chroma = U·sin(t) + V·cos(t)<br />&quot;Delayed Chroma by 90 degrees&quot; → U·cos(t) - V·sin(t)<br />Composte + &quot;Delayed Chroma by 90 degrees&quot; = Luma + U(sin(t)+cos(t)) + V(cos(t)-sin(t)) = Luma + U·sin(t+π÷4)÷√2 + V·cos(t+π÷4)÷√2<br /><br />That would just increase the saturation of the chroma signal.</div><br /><br />It would roll off the lower sideband of the color carrier, while keeping the upper sideband intact.

		

